<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="239" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[178,1086,1022,1177]" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: prominent) alludes to the pronounced median granule of the male tergite III.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="239" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[178,1085,1192,1272]" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">
Description: Abdomen completely blackish; antennomere I blackish-brown, as dark as antennomeres II-XI or nearly so. Other external characters (
<figureCitation box="[882,1020,1221,1243]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Figs 117-118</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[178,309,1250,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberifera">
<emphasis box="[178,309,1250,1272]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">N. tuberifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[178,1085,1288,1485]" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">
♂: tergite III with pronounced median protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[732,822,1288,1310]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Fig. 119</figureCitation>
); tergite VII with weakly pronounced median elevation, this elevation with denser punctation and more distinct microreticulation; tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[499,638,1346,1368]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Figs 120-121</figureCitation>
) with truncate and weakly crenulate posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[465,557,1375,1398]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Fig. 122</figureCitation>
) longer than tergite VIII and strongly projecting posteriorly, middle of posterior margin truncate; median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[941,1078,1405,1427]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Figs 123-124</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[178,272,1434,1456]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="0.53">0.53 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process and internal structures of distinctive shapes; paramere longer than median lobe and with moderately slender apical lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[178,1084,1500,1552]" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">
<specimenCount box="[178,199,1506,1527]" pageId="32" pageNumber="239" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[344,431,1500,1523]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
) with strongly convex posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[990,1077,1501,1523]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Fig. 126</figureCitation>
) broadly convex posteriorly; spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[605,691,1530,1552]" captionStart="Figs 117-127" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1482,1504]" captionTargetBox="[194,1072,212,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-1@33.[186,1076,212,1473]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 117-127: Nepalota prominula nov.sp.: (117) forebody; (118) antenna; (119) anterior portion of male abdomen; (120) male tergite VIII; (121) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (122) male sternite VIII; (123-124) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (125) female tergite VIII; (126) female sternite VIII; (127) spermatheca. Scale bars: 117: 1.0 mm; 119-120, 122, 125- 126: 0.5 mm; 123-124, 127: 0.2 mm; 121: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414218/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="239">Fig. 127</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity box="[857,934,1530,1551]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
